# Uicollective UI Conventions

- Organize each page with its own section component folder, for example `components/about/*`.
- Page files should compose imported sections rather than containing all section markup inline.
- Use semantic Tailwind v4 tokens from `src/styles/global.css` instead of ad hoc color classes.
- Never use Tailwind `@apply` in this project.
- Treat `mt-*` as the default spacing utility and avoid `mb-*`.
- Keep section spacing consistent through per-section `Wrapper` usage and top-margin rhythm.
- Prefer existing `Button` variants instead of inline button styling.
- Prefer `Text` variants instead of hardcoded typography patterns when possible.
- Do not add eyebrow labels or uppercase tracked helper text.
- Do not use `tracking-wide`.
- Do not design sections around colored background bands.
- Make responsive behavior with CSS first and vanilla JavaScript only when needed.
